<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Comment on Serb Attack, NATO Airstrike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Comment on Serb Attack, NATO Airstrike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Cetin Places Moral Responsibility on NATO </H4>

<F P=102> TA1004154394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 10 apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1004154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 10 (AA) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin said on Sunday [10 April] that the United Nations will be 
under moral blame if the claims that say Serbia carried out a 
chemical attack on Gorazde become true. 
  Cetin said he called Bosnian Premier Haris Silajdzic on the 
phone to talk about the developments happening in Bosnia and 
added that Silajdzic said during their searches in hospitals, 
they haven't met any evidence that chemical weapon was used in 
Gorazde. 
  Cetin said there is no specific information that chemical 
weapons were used and the number of casualties in Gorazde were 
not known either. 
  The foreign minister said NATO was ready for intervention 
however they haven't yet received any order from the UN 
representative in Bosnia. 
  Cetin recalled that the situation in Gorazde was discussed 
during a Turkish-Bosnian-Croatian tripartite meeting which was 
held earlier this week "we called for the UN to take necessary 
measures against the situation" he added. 
  "We have completed our preparations to call NATO and the UN 
Security Council for a meeting if the claims come true" Cetin 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

