<F P=102>   LD1104095994 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] French Cooperation Minister Michel Roussin said late 
yesterday afternoon that French troops would not remain in 
Rwanda after the evacuation operation. Last night he was at 
Roissy airport, near Paris, where he welcomed the first French 
evacuees. He declared that the operation could already be 
considered a success. 
  [Begin Roussin recording] I would like to use this occasion 
to thank the troops and the crews of the military transport 
units who made the necessary planes available and made it 
possible to evacuate French nationals to Bujumbura and Bangui. 
We were helped by the people of the Central African Republic 
[CAR] and of Burundi: This has to be mentioned. Both in Bangui 
and in Burundi, we were welcomed by our friends. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

