<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rwandan Patriotic Front Demands French Neutrality </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rwandan Patriotic Front Demands French Neutrality </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004130694 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1100 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1004130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation in Rwanda is complicated by the fact 
that the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] rebels have given a 
warning to France and to other Western countries. They have 
asked them to be neutral in this ethnic war. Francois 
Rutayisire, the RPF representative in Paris is quite unambiguous: 
  [Begin Rutayisire recording] Three years ago, France sent in 
its troops, saying they were there to protect and evacuate 
French nationals. They ended up staying for three years. We 
hope this is not going to be the same. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] If on their way to Kigali, RPF 
troops come into contact with French troops barring their way, 
will they react violently? 
  [Rutayisire] One of our spokesmen has already answered this 
question. If anyone gets in the way of the RPF forces, who are 
fighting to eliminate the presidential Guard, the RPF will not 
hesitate to fight. 
  [Correspondent] Including against French troops? 
  [Rutayisire] Against whoever gets in its way. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

