<F P=102>   AU0804170994 Paris AFP in English 1430 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0804170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, April 8 (AFP) -- French firm Dassault 
Automatismes et Telecommunications (of the Dassault Electronique 
Group) on Friday [8 April] announced signature of a contract for 
supplying a complete wireless digital telephony system for the 
city of Chongqing, in Sichuan Province, southwestern China. 
  It did not indicate the value of the contract. 
  The announcement indicated that the network for Chongqing 
will be the equivalent of the French "Bi-Bop" cordless 
telephone, used by some pedestrians in Paris and other areas to 
make calls from wherever they happen to be. 

</TEXT>

