<H3> <TI>   UNPROFOR Source Says NATO To Carry Out New Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNPROFOR Source Says NATO To Carry Out New Air Strikes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104122994 Paris AFP in English 1218 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1104122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, April 11 (AFP) -- NATO warplanes will 
shortly carry out new air strikes on Bosnian Serb positions 
around the besieged Moslem town of Gorazde, a UN Protection 
Force (UNPROFOR) headquarters staffer said here Monday [11 
April]. 
  The air strikes had been ordered after the Serbs resumed 
shelling of the town, hitting the hospital and a building where 
UN military observers were housed, the UN staffer in the 
operations room said, asking not to be named. 
  UN Protection Force spokesman Captain Eric Chaperon 
dismissed 
the report as untrue, but sources close to NATO said planes had 
taken off and were flying low over Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

