<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy `Gatecrashes' Liberal Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy `Gatecrashes' Liberal Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104141694 Paris AFP in English 1329 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1104141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Strasbourg, April 11 (AFP) -- Maverick Russian MP 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy had a row with European assemblymen here 
on Monday [11 April] when he gatecrashed a political party 
gathering. 
  He got into a meeting of the 44-strong liberal grouping, 
which had, however, written to him asking him to stay away from 
Strasbourg because of his extremist right-wing nationalist 
views. Zhirinovskiy's movement calls itself the Russian Liberal 
Democratic Party and scored a striking success in December's 
general election. 
  Asked to leave the room, Zhirinovskiy berated the group as 
"CIA agents afraid to have a democratic debate." He added, "I 
was not invited here to drink champagne." 
  The liberal MP's walked out. 
  Zhirinovskiy is part of the 18-strong Russian delegation 
attending the Council of Europe's latest parliamentary assembly. 
Russia has had "special guest" status since 1990. 
  Assembly speaker Miguel Angel Martinez commented that 
Zhirinovskiy was "certainly not the most important" member of 
the Russian team. 
  The Russian MP earlier complained that France had given him 
a 
visa confining him to Strasbourg, and said that restriction on 
his movements was a violation of his rights as a Russian member 
of parliament. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

