<H3> <TI>   European Commission Earmarks Aid for Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    European Commission Earmarks Aid for Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1104152594 Brussels BELGA Database in French 1111 GMT 11 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1104152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA Database </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed LVE (CET): "Crisis -- Emergency Aid for </F>
Rwanda"] 
  [Excerpt] Brussels, 11 Apr (BELGA) -- "The European 
Commission (EC) unblocked emergency aid worth ECU500,000 (20 
million Belgian francs) to help the victims of the fresh wave of 
interethnic violence that is sweeping through the country," 
announced a EC spokesman on Monday [11 April]. 
  This aid would go toward the dispatching of medical and 
surgical equipment to be placed at the disposal of teams of 
Belgian "Medecins Sans Frontieres" [Doctors Wtihout Borders] who 
are already there on the ground. 
  "This equipment was already sent on its way Saturday from 
Rotterdam airport," specified the spokesman. "In fact, it would 
be the first of several consignments of emergency aid which 
would follow in the days or weeks to come," he added. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

