<F P=106> [Article signed JCH/ALN: "Full Text of Official Press </F>
Release of Limited Belgian Council of Ministers Meeting"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 8 Apr (BELGA) -- "The government met with 
Prime Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene in the chair, to review the 
situation in Rwanda. 
  ``The government rendered homage to the courage of the 
Belgian troops serving in UNAMIR [UN Peacekeeping Force in 
Rwanda]. It expressed its indignation at the murder of ten 
Belgian blue helmets who died while peacefully carrying out 
their mission. He repeated his deep condolences to the victims' 
families. 
  ``On behalf of the government, the prime minister and the 
foreign minister have expressed to UN General Secretary 
Butrus-Ghali, through personal contacts, the imperative need to 
reinforce the safety of UN forces in Rwanda. The secretary 
general fully shares this concern. 
  ``The government is moreover extremely concerned about the 
deterioration of the local situation, and particularly the 
threats against our compatriots. In consequence, it has decided 
on the necessary measures to be taken to guarantee the safety of 
Belgian nationals. A crisis center has been opened at the 
Foreign Ministry.'' 

