<F P=106> [Article signed DGO/ADB: "Rwanda -- Return of First </F>
Repatriated Belgians"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 11 Apr (BELGA)-- The first aircraft 
bringing Belgian nationals back from Rwanda landed at Brussels 
national airport on Monday morning [11 April] at approximately 
0215 GMT. 
  The Sabena aircraft, a Boeing 737 that took off from 
Bujumbura, the capital of Burundi, had 89 Belgians and 26 
Netherlanders on board. The Netherlanders continued their 
journey to the Netherlands immediately, while the Belgians were 
taken to the Queen Astrid Military Hospital in 
Neder-over-Hembeek, where their families were waiting for them. 
The Federal Government was represented by Vice Prime Minister 
Elio di Rupo. 
  According to Sabena, the next repatriation flight, this time 
on board a DC-10 coming from Nairobi, Kenya, is scheduled to 
land at 2300 GMT. 

</TEXT>

