<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Government has welcomed 
the NATO air strike against Serbian positions near the east 
Bosnian Muslim enclave of Gorazde. This was an understandable 
step taken by the United Nations, Government Spokesman Dieter 
Vogel stated in Bonn on Monday. The Serbian side had been 
warned but failed to heed the warning. Bonn was hoping that the 
Serbs would now come to reason and that the hostilities could be 
ended quickly. Vogel would not comment on the Russian protests 
against the military action. He said that the Federal 
Government recognized them. 

