<H3> <TI>   Germans Still `Trapped' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Germans Still `Trapped' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104140994 Hamburg DPA in German 1255 GMT 11 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- According to information provided by 
the Foreign Ministry Monday noon [11 April], 11 Germans are 
still stuck in the Deutsche Welle relay station near the Rwandan 
capital Kigali. Foreign Ministry Spokesman Michael Geerdts 
stated that the hostilities were continuing nearby and that the 
access road was mined. At the moment one was examining several 
options to evacuate the trapped Germans, one of which was to 
rescue them by air by helicopter. 
  The Foreign Ministry has thus confuted reports that the 11 
Germans -- seven engineers, three spouses, and one child -- had 
already been flown out of the station by U.S. soldiers. This 
had been said by the director of Deutsche Welle, Dieter Weirich, 
in Cologne earlier today. 

</TEXT>

