<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Defense Minister Arrives for 3-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ukrainian Defense Minister Arrives for 3-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104114894 Hamburg DPA in German 1041 GMT 11 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- Defense Minister Volker Ruehe (Christian 
Democratic Union) welcomed his Ukrainian counterpart Vitaliy 
Radetsky at the Defense Ministry with military honors this 
morning. Radetsky has started a three-day visit of the 
Bundeswehr in Germany. He wants to continue the dialogue on 
security policy that Ruehe initiated with a visit to Ukraine 
last year. At the time, the two ministers signed an agreement 
on military cooperation between the Ukrainian and German Armed 
Forces. 
  Immediately after the welcoming ceremony, the ministers 
began 
their exchange of views on the continuation of the contacts. 
They also discussed the development of a European security 
structure and cooperation between Kiev and NATO. Ukraine 
belongs to the 14 East European countries that have voted in 
favor of close military and political cooperation with the 
Western alliance as a result of the NATO initiative Partnership 
for Peace. In the next few days, Radetsky will also visit 
Bundeswehr units in Nirvenich and Hemer. 

</TEXT>

