<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Urges Turkey To Observe Human Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Urges Turkey To Observe Human Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0904165494 Hamburg DPA in German 1107 GMT 9 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0904165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the view of Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel, 
Turkey must be openly reminded to keep human rights -- 
"especially because we have had friendly relations with Turkey 
for decades, because it is our partner in NATO and has an 
important bridging function." In an interview with BILD AM 
SONNTAG, Kinkel said: "Yes, there are human rights violations 
in Turkey." 
  Kinkel once again said that delinquent Kurds should only be 
deported in absolutely exceptional cases. Anyone who commits a 
crime belongs before a court and in prison. The government is 
currently examining whether it is safeguarded that those that 
are deported will not face torture, death penalties, or 
anti-constitutional treatment. 

</TEXT>

