<H3> <TI>   SPD Supports Deportations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Supports Deportations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104145694 Hamburg DPA in German 1340 GMT 11 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Monday [11 April], the Social Democratic Party 
of Germany [SPD] Presidium -- like party chairman Rudolf 
Scharping previously -- advocated the deportation of Kurdish 
delinquents. However, it can only take place when an examination 
in each individual case has shown that the person to be deported 
neither has to fear torture nor capital punishment in Turkey, 
the party leadership stated. The struggle for the Kurds' 
self-determination has to be carried out with democratic and 
nonviolent means. In particular, the valid German laws have to 
be observed and respected, it was stated. 
  The SPD again criticized the FRG Government because of arms 
supplies from former GDR stocks to Ankara. A government led by 
the SPD will discontinue all deliveries of military material to 
Turkey, it was stated. 

</TEXT>

