<H3> <TI>   Eichel Attacks Kanther's Stance on Republikaner </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Eichel Attacks Kanther's Stance on Republikaner </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804200794 Hamburg DPA in German 1540 GMT 8 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0804200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hamburg -- In connection with the debate on 
banning the right-wing extremist Republikaner, Hesse's 
Minister-President Hans Eichel (Social Democratic Party) has 
accused Federal Interior Minister Manfred Kanther (Christian 
Democratic Union) of "making the Republikaner acceptable." 
Unless Kanther lists the Republikaner as right-wing extremist 
party in the next Office for the Protection of the Constitution 
report, he will work directly into the hands of the enemies of 
democracy, Eichel said in Wiesbaden on Friday [8 April]. In 
Eichel's view, there is sufficient evidence of Republikaner 
members participating in violent acts against foreigners. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

