<H3> <TI>   SPD Demands Information About Eurofighter Costs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Demands Information About Eurofighter Costs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804081394 Hamburg DPA in German 2303 GMT 7 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0804081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Osnabrueck (DPA) -- In connection with the 
financing of the Eurofighter 2000, the Social Democratic Party 
of Germany [SPD] has made serious accusations against Defense 
Minister Volker Ruehe (Christian Democratic Union). In an 
interview with NEUE OSNABRUECKER ZEITUNG (Friday edition), SPD 
defense expert Walter Kolbow said that the ministry has 
confirmed reports that the thrift version of the Eurofighter, 
which Ruehe pushed through, gives rise to considerable 
additional costs for development because of the necessary 
changes. The SPD will demand clarification of the matter at a 
Defense Committee meeting next Wednesday [13 April]. 
  Deutschlandfunk radio reported that the German share alone 
in 
the costs of the four-nation project will rise by at least 300 
million German marks [DM]. An expert report by the Federal 
Audit Office even gave the additional costs as DM700 million. 
Kolbow stressed that the combat plane will force Ruehe "to give 
a political and financial oath of disclosure." The minister 
must be aware of the fact that the Bundestag will not approve 
one pfennig more than planned for the development of the 
Eurofighter. Even disregarding the now mentioned additional 
costs, Ruehe does not know how to pay for the plane's 
development. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

