  [Text] Ankara (DPA) -- On Monday [11 April], Turkey warned 
Germany against "provocations and anti-Turkish propaganda from 
the camp of the opponents of good German-Turkish relations." 
Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin said in Ankara on Monday 
that "normal military cooperation" will also continue after last 
Thursday's halting of arms deliveries. The auxiliary supplies 
within the framework of NATO defense aid are affected. 
  Cetin affirmed that Turkey continues to adhere to the 
conditions and is using the BTR-60 and BTR-80 armored personnel 
carriers supplied by Germany from the stocks of the GDR People's 
Army in the internal controversy with Kurdish extremists from 
the ranks of the Workers Party of Kurdistan (PKK). He thinks it 
is completely normal that the FRG Government is taking the time 
to follow up on the accusations because of the tremendous 
domestic policy pressure and to examine whether the arms 
delivered from Germany were used in violation of the agreements, 
which, however, is not the case. 

