<H3> <TI>   Bonn To Freeze Development Aid for Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn To Freeze Development Aid for Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104145794 Paris AFP in English 1429 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1104145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, April 11 (AFP) -- Germany has decided to 
freeze 83 million marks (49 million dollars) in planned 
development aid for Rwanda in the light of developments in that 
strife-torn country, the Economic Cooperation Ministry said here 
on Monday [11 April]. 
  Cooperation Minister Carl-Dieter Spranger said cooperation 
was currently out of the question because of fighting. 
  The aid, promised at the end of 1993, relates primarily to 
agriculture, infrastructure work, health, and education. 

</TEXT>

