<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   FDP Favors Continued Government Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FDP Favors Continued Government Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104124794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1148 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The FDP [Free Democratic Party] 
presidium has said it is in favor of continuing the German 
Government coalition with the union parties [Christian 
Democratic Union and Christian Social Union]. FDP Chairman Klaus 
Kinkel announced this in Bonn today. A proposal to that effect 
is to be submitted to the FDP federal party conference to be 
held in Rostock in June, he says. 

</TEXT>

