<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Bosnia, the situation appears to be quieter in 
the region of Gorazde following yesterday's second NATO air 
strike on Serb tanks shelling the Muslim enclave. Bosnians 
welcome this show of force. 
  Alain Lamassoure, the French minister delegate of European 
affairs said this morning [on Radio Monte Carlo] that the 
bombing of Serb positions should be extended if the latter were 
to continue their attacks on the Gorazde safe haven. The carrot 
and the stick must be used, Lamassoure added. 

