<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Airline Officials Say Juppe Bomb Alert `False' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Airline Officials Say Juppe Bomb Alert `False' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104181194 Paris AFP in English 1735 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1104181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bordeaux, France, April 11 (AFP) -- A bomb alert 
that turned out to be a false alarm was reported Monday [11 
April] on a commercial jet carrying French Foreign Minister 
Alain Juppe, airline officials said. 
  The French domestic airline Air Inter said the Airbus 300 
carrying 306 people was halfway between Paris and Bordeaux when 
an anonymous caller to Paris' Orly airport said there was a bomb 
on board. 
  The pilot decided to continue the flight, and all the 
passengers were evacuated as soon as the jet landed in Bordeaux 
in southwest France. 
  A search of the aircraft turned up no bomb. 
  Juppe was traveling to Bordeaux to inaugurate an 
organization 
designed to boost trade between regional companies and 
international firms. 

</TEXT>

