<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister on Zhirinovskiy's `Delirious Threats' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister on Zhirinovskiy's `Delirious Threats' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104171594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1637 GMT 
11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The absurb and delirious threats made by Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy, whose presence in Strasbourg seems out-of-tune and 
gauche, do not intimidate us." 
  These were the words of Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri, who 
was replying to statements made by the Russian ultra-nationalist 
leader condemning the raids on Serb positions in the town of 
Gorazde, which were carried out by two F-18 [as received] 
bombers belonging to NATO forces. The planes left from Aviano, 
in Friuli. 
  "Italy," stressed Fabbri, "guarantees its participation in 
all legitimate NATO and UN operations that protect UNPROFOR 
units and avert the massacre of civilians." 

</TEXT>

