<H3> <TI>   Aho Comments on `Successful' PRC Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aho Comments on `Successful' PRC Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104162894 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1430 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finnish Prime Minister Esko Aho has described his 
visit to China as extraordinarily successful. Aho, who returned 
home this afternoon, said before leaving Beijing that Finland 
and China had a good chance to increase their cooperation, 
particularly in the forestry industry, in the energy sector, and 
in environmental protection. Aho said that during the visit 
Finland did not want to make an issue of China's human rights 
policy. 
  [Begin Aho recording] These individual cases, which have 
received quite extensive publicity, were not raised in the talks 
we conducted, and it has not been part of our tradition to 
discuss them in political talks either. We concentrated on a 
more general level on discussing human rights and political 
rights and voiced our views on that. In other words, this issue 
was not discussed. 
  Our basic attitude to human rights issues is similar to that 
of France and other West European countries. Our attitude to 
human rights issues is, in principle, similar, but it must be 
admitted that there have been and are differences in the 
approach between Finland and many West European countries. [end 
recording] 
  The high-level visits between Finland and China will resume 
as early as this spring. Chairman of the Chinese People's 
Congress Li Ruihuan [title as heard] will pay a visit to Finland 
in May. 

</TEXT>

