<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Claims No Prior Knowledge of NATO Raid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104125794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1104125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Replying to questions about the U.S. raid in 
Gorazde, government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said the facts 
are not yet clear. The spokesman also stressed that we must 
seek a just, quick, and viable solution of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina problem based on respect for international 
law and the decisions of international organizations. 
  Replying to another question, Venizelos said Greece was not 
informed of the raid beforehand and added that not every NATO 
country is informed before similar acts. There is no provision 
for any similar process involving deliberations, he said, adding 
that the order was given by Akasi, meaning it was actually an 
order by the UN secretary general. 

</TEXT>

