<H3> <TI>   17 November Targeted UK Aircraft Carrier </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    17 November Targeted UK Aircraft Carrier </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104154294 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1104154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The British aircraft carrier Ark Royal, which was 
anchored in Piraievs last weekend, was to be the third target of 
the 17 November terrorist organziation, which claimed 
responsibility for the attacks against the offices of two 
insurance companies on Kifissia Avenue last night. 
  In a telephone call to a private radio station, 17 November 
stated that it was also going to strike at the aircraft carrier. 
At 1230 today, a passerby accidentally found two 2.3-inch 
rockets in a metal pipe and a firing mechanism on a building 
site along the Miaoulis coast in Piraievs. The rockets were 
defused by explosives experts. 

</TEXT>

