<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin Says Gorazde UN Intervention `Too Late' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Says Gorazde UN Intervention `Too Late' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104163094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1550 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1104163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 11 (A.A.) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin on Monday [11 April] critized the United Nations mechanism 
as being too slow, saying it was the reason why intervention to 
Gorazde had come too late. 
  He was speaking to reporters after a joint press conference 
with visiting Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres. 
  Cetin said necessary protection should also be given to 
other 
regions besides Sarajevo, stressing that Turkey had called to 
attention the fact that Gorazde was a "critical" region, before 
the Serbian attacks were intensified. 
  He underlined the fact that Serbs in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
should join the agreement signed between Bosnians and Croats, 
adding a healthy future for the Balkans can only be reached with 
the setting up of lasting and just peace. 
  Cetin said Turkey will continue efforts for the 
establishment 
of peace in the region adding talks between Turkish-Bosnian and 
Croatian delegations will be held at the foreign ministers level. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

