<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] After a news conference, 
Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres was received by President 
Suleyman Demirel at the Cankaya Mansion. According to a 
statement issued by the Presidential Press Center, Peres 
conveyed to Demirel messages of friendship from Israeli 
President Ezer Weizman and Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin. The 
statement added that at the meeting, which was also attended by 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin, Peres briefed Demirel on the 
developments in the region and the Israeli-Palestinian peace 
talks. Peres told Demirel that progress has been achieved at 
the peace talks. At the meeting views were also exchanged on 
regional and international issues concerning both countries. 
  Peres was also received by Prime Minister Tansu Ciller. 

