<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Leaves for Talks in Syria </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister Leaves for Talks in Syria </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104171494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1600 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1104171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 11 (A.A.) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese left for Syria on Monday [11 April] for an official 
visit as the guest of his Syrian counterpart Muhammad Harbah. 
  He told reporters before his departure at Ankara's Esenboga 
Airport that during his stay bilateral security issues will be 
discussed as well as regional and international developments. 
  Mentese said in order to develop present friendly relations 
and cooperation ties both sides will try to solve any problems 
that are included within the boundaries of previously signed 
agreements or that remain outside its scope. 
  He also expressed belief that relations will go further with 
this visit, adding that "everything" will be discussed during 
his stay. 
  Mentese and accompanying delegation will return to Turkey on 
April 13. 

</TEXT>

