<H3> <TI>   Bank Governor on Economic Stability Program Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bank Governor on Economic Stability Program Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104113694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Central Bank Governor Yaman Toruner in Ankara </F>
on 11 April 1994 -- recorded] 
  [Text] The Extended Administrative Council of the Turkish 
Union of Banks, the Central Bank, and the Treasury and Foreign 
Trade Undersecretariat held a meeting yesterday, 10 April 1994. 
At the meeting, they stressed that they share the view that the 
economic stability program is the guarantee of the future of 
Turkey's economy. 
  They also determined that there is no liquidity problem in 
terms of either the Turkish lira or foreign exchange in the 
Turkish banking system. They decided to make the system 
liquidity permanent by means of measures to be determined by the 
Turkish Union of Banks and the Central Bank and to be carried 
out by all the banks that are members of the union. 
  The participants at the meeting agreed that publishing the 
recent speculative and unfounded reports in connection with 
certain banks is, to say the least, immoral. They stressed that 
both the Treasury and Foreign Trade Undersecretariat and the 
banks concerned will take legal action in connection with these 
reports. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

