<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ruehe Says Bosnia NATO Strikes `Necessary' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ruehe Says Bosnia NATO Strikes `Necessary' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104174494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1625 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Defense Minister Volker 
Ruehe has justified as "absolutely necessary" the attacks 
carried out by NATO combat aircraft on Serbian positions on 
behalf of the United Nations. It was obvious that the Serbs 
would only understand "this clear language," Ruehe said in an 
interview with the daily DIE WELT (Tuesday [12 April] edition). 
A "human catastrophe on an immense scale" was beginning to 
emerge in Gorazde. Now everybody has to exert an influence on 
the Serbs to stop their attacks. Russia could also continue to 
play an important role in this process, the minister stressed in 
the article, which was released in advance of publication by the 
Federal Defense Ministry. 
  Hitherto the United Nations has had neither the legal nor 
the 
practical opportunities to actively disarm the Serb besiegers. 
It is therefore all the more important now to exploit all the 
opportunities in Bosnia, "where the United Nations could fall 
back on NATO's resources." This means military air operations 
in particular, Ruehe said. Neither the civilian population nor 
UN troops must come to harm during this. Ruehe once again 
stressed that the deployment of German soldiers in the former 
Yugoslavia will "not be considered" for historical reasons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

