<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe: No UN Retreat From `Provocations' in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe: No UN Retreat From `Provocations' in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104223994 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2200 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104223994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The situation in Bosnia: things are somewhat 
calmer this evening in Gorazde. [passage omitted] 
  Foreign Minister Alain Juppe said this evening that the 
allies would not retreat when faced with provocations or attacks 
in Bosnia, wherever they came from. Alain Juppe spoke to Alain 
Pages of Radio France Bordeaux-Gironde: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] The resolutions of the Security 
Council and the decisions of the alliance are very clear: they 
authorize UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] to ask for the use of 
air strikes when it believes that our soldiers on the ground are 
under threat. These conditions were fulfilled in Gorazde. 
  If the conditions that occurred in Gorazde should, alas, 
happen again, if UNPROFOR is attacked, if one side or another, 
let us say the Serbs, do not respect the decisions taken by the 
United Nations, then of course air strikes must be used. We 
must make it clear that we shall not retreat when faced with 
provocations and attacks. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

