<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iran's Foreign Minister Velayati Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iran's Foreign Minister Velayati Begins Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Expresses Anxiety Over Bosnia </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104100994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Velayati arrived in Austria at noon 
today and immediately began his first round of talks with 
Austrian Foreign Minister Mr. Mock in Vienna. In the meeting, 
discussions were held about the expansion of bilateral ties in 
various fields, and about regional and international issues, 
such as Palestine and Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  The foreign ministers of Austria and the Islamic Republic of 
Iran expressed their anxiety in the meeting about the 
continuation of the killings in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

