<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Arrives in Bonn for Talks With Kohl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Butrus-Ghali Arrives in Bonn for Talks With Kohl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204151894 Hamburg DPA in German 1412 GMT 12 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali 
arrived for an official visit to Bonn on Tuesday [12 April] 
following an invitation by Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl. In 
his talks, which started with a meeting with Foreign Minister 
Klaus Kinkel and are scheduled to continue on Wednesday in a 
meeting with Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl, the UN secretary 
general intends to encourage Germany's participation in a 
permanent UN reaction force. The Germans have announced that 
they were seeking closer cooperation with and within the United 
Nations, including a seat on the Security Council, and the 
transfer of UN organizations to Bonn. Butrus-Ghali will also 
meet members of parliament before his departure scheduled for 
Wednesday afternoon. 

</TEXT>

