<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Calls For Clear Definition of Bundeswehr Task </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Calls For Clear Definition of Bundeswehr Task </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204154494 Hamburg DPA in German 1233 GMT 12 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [no dateline as received] -- Klaus Kinkel, foreign 
minister and Free Democratic Party of Germany [FDP] chairman, 
has called for a clear definition of the Bundeswehr's assigment. 
At a meeting with the Executive Committee of the Bundeswehr 
Association, Kinkel was quoted by the FDP press office as saying 
that "permanently playing around with figures" regarding the 
strength of the Bundeswehr is wrong. Kinkel clearly rejected 
the reasoning that the size, structure, and efficiency of the 
Bundeswehr should mainly be determined by the availablity of 
state funds. In the meeting, FDP Secretary General Werner Hoyer 
emphasized that the Armed Forces are "not light switches that 
can be turned on or off according to short-term fluctuations in 
demand." 

</TEXT>

