<H3> <TI>   Norway, Sweden, Finland Conclude EU Membership Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Norway, Sweden, Finland Conclude EU Membership Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204192894 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1800 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Norway and Sweden have concluded in Brussels the 
texts of the agreements on the conditions of EU membership. 
Norway managed to get its demands on fishing concessions 
included in the text of the agreement. The fishing questions 
concerning Sweden's agreement were also solved a little while 
ago. And the STT [Finnish Telegraph Agency] is reporting right 
now that the text of the Finnish membership agreement has now 
also been concluded. Austria concluded its negotiations last 
night. The negotiations were urgent because the texts of the 
agreements must be presented to the European Parliament today so 
that the Parliament can vote on new members on 4 May. 

</TEXT>

