<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Calls For Participation in UN Operations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel Calls For Participation in UN Operations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304100394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0817 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1304100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has 
reiterated that in the future Germany has to be involved without 
reservation in UN operations to secure world peace. Despite 
setbacks, the United Nations was becoming "the central guardian 
of peace for the human race," Kinkel said at the annual 
conference of the German Society for Defense Technology in Bonn 
today. Germany should not stand to one side in this, and has to 
"come down from the spectators gallery." The foreign minister 
added that the greater responsibility that Germany will be 
taking on also makes necessary a "corresponding voice" as a 
permanent member of the UN Security Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

