<H3> <TI>   Republikaner Officials Reportedly Protect Skinheads </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Republikaner Officials Reportedly Protect Skinheads </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304091594 Munich FOCUS in German 11 Apr 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> AU1304091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich FOCUS </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Top Republikaner Candidate Protects </F>
Skinheads"] 
  [Text] Uwe Goller, land chairman and top candidate of the 
North Rhine-Westphalian Republikaner for the European election, 
has obviously covered up the fact that party colleagues of his 
were involved in an attack on an asylum-seeker's hostel. This 
can be concluded from documents available to the North 
Rhine-Westphalian Office for the Protection of the Constitution. 
  On 7 October 1991, skinheads attacked a temporary housing 
camp in Bergheim near Cologne. The perpetrators managed to 
escape. 
  Two years later, the Executive Committee of the Republikaner 
in the Mittelrhein district discussed the involvement of a 
leading functionary in the attack. According to the minutes of 
the meeting, a party member declared in lieu of an oath that the 
functionary had told him that he had planned the attack, 
participated in it, and then hid his friends in his basement. 
Land Chairman Goller was informed. He and his deputy met with 
the "denouncer." The result: The man withdrew his statement. 
Despite the findings about Republikaner involvement in crimes, 
North Rhine-Westphalian Interior Minister Schnoor (Social 
Democratic Party of Germany) does not want to apply for a ban: 
"The party must be opposed by political means." 

</TEXT>

