<H3> <TI>   FAZ Indicator Shows Widespread Economic Recovery </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FAZ Indicator Shows Widespread Economic Recovery </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204173594 Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE in German 
12 Apr 94 p 15 </F>

<F P=103> AU1204173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "FAZ Indicator: Broad-Based </F>
Recovery"] 
  [Text] Frankfurt/Main, 11 Apr -- The recovery of the FAZ 
[FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE ZEITUNG] economic development indicator 
continued with unchanged speed in February. With a value of 
108.0, the previous month's level was exceeded by 1.2 percent; 
compared to the corresponding month last year, the growth 
amounted to 8 percent. With the exception of the FAZ share 
index, which again went down slightly following the speedy 
increase at the end of 1993, all individual elements included in 
the indicator were clearly pointing upward. Thus, the economic 
recovery, which has been noted by the FAZ indicator for almost a 
year now, is spreading further. The opportunities for economic 
recovery in the course of this year have thus improved further. 
The increase confidence is particularly obvious in industry; 
the Ifo business climate index once again improved tangibly. 
After a temporary period of weakness at the turn of the year, 
orders received are clearly pointing upward, too. Particularly 
gratifying is the fact that domestic orders have, for the first 
time, clearly increased again. The positive development of 
foreign demand has continued. In addition to the economic 
improvement in important trading partner countries, the real 
external value of the German mark has declined further. A 
positive effect on the economic development is also exerted by 
the fact that the interest structure, which has been largely 
inverse since the turn of the year, has meanwhile disappeared 
almost completely. In total, the prospects are good that the 
Bundesbank will continue its policy of a cautious reduction of 
short-term interests over the next few months. The number of 
FAZ job offers seems to have overcome its low point, even though 
recovery is still very moderate in this field. 

</TEXT>

