<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calls for Greater U.S., Russian Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls for Greater U.S., Russian Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204173194 Paris AFP in English 1716 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1204173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, April 12 (AFP) -- France proposed on Tuesday 
[12 April] that Russia and the United States assume a bigger 
role in the international peace conference on former Yugoslavia, 
currently chaired by the European Union [EU] and the United 
Nations. 
  France also said it was examining the possibility of a UN 
Security Council resolution on the besieged Moslem enclave of 
Gorazde providing for an immediate ceasefire and deployment of 
UN peacekeepers, accompanied by a Serbian pullback "without 
delay and without conditions." 
  Opening a National Assembly debate on Bosnia, French Foreign 
Minister Alain Juppe said France would propose to its EU 
partners that Russia and the U.S. share the co-chairmanship of 
the Yugoslavia conference. 
  "Each of the three main partners, the United States, Europe 
and Russia, must recognise that it cannot resolve the problem 
alone," Juppe said. 
  The foreign minister also said the the Security Council 
resolution should call for an immediate ceasefire and 
"deployment on the ground of UN Protection Forces to separate 
the two communities." [passage omitted] 
  "We must fix precise political aims for our action in 
Gorazde 
as was the case in Sarajevo," where the threat of NATO attacks 
forced back Serbian forces and lifted their siege, Juppe said. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

