<H3> <TI>   Leotard Comments on Gorazde Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leotard Comments on Gorazde Air Strikes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204213594 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2030 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204213594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There was a debate on Bosnia at the National 
Assembly this afternoon. France may submit a resolution on 
Gorazde to the Security Council, according to Alain Juppe, the 
minister of foreign affairs. 
  Francois Leotard also addressed the Assembly. The minister 
of defense justified the intervention by allied planes against 
the Serbs in Gorazde. Francois Leotard: 
  [Begin Leotard recording] We could not allow the attacks on 
Gorazde to continue, especially those of these last few days. 
We will not permit Gorazde to become another Vukovar. 
  The events in Gorazde doubtless mark another turning point 
in 
the Balkan crisis. Either the determination of the 
international community will be understood by all the factions, 
then the road will be open for fighting to be suspended, and 
negotiations to start again. Or the opposite will happen: The 
obstinacy of some people, perhaps too the orders of some 
military factions, will make the use of force necessary again, 
with the increase in military might that this would imply and 
the risks that one can imagine would result. 
  Ladies and gentlemen, I have repeated several times that 
there can be no military solution to the Bosnian conflict. [end 
recording] 

