Daily Report 
<DATE1>  13 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chief Fininvest TV News Editors Resign in Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chief Fininvest TV News Editors Resign in Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304112294 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1030 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mentana, Fede, and Liguori, the chief editors of the 
news bulletins broadcast on the three Fininvest-controlled 
television channels [Canale Cinque, Retequattro, and Italia Uno] 
handed in their resignations a short time ago as a protest 
against the statements made by Franco Tato, the managing 
director of the Fininvest group. He told a newspaper that if 
the Mammi Law [telecommunications law approved last year by 
parliament] did not exist, he would have cancelled all the news 
and information programs on the three channels. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-19065 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu071_j_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-071 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
