<F P=104>  Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE </F>
<F P=105>  Danish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Erik Bjorn Moller: "United Nations Will Not </F>
Hesitate To Strike"] 
  [Text] Danish Foreign Minister Niels Helveg Petersen fully 
backs the decision to bomb Serb positions near the Bosnian town 
of Gorazde. 
  "In the light of the information made available, it is clear 
that it was the correct decision and the Serbs should not be 
surprised. The UN Security Council has decided that the United 
Nations may ask for air support -- and this is what has 
happened. The UN forces in the region have felt themselves hard 
pressed and have therefore asked for air support," the Danish 
foreign minister said. 
  He stressed that the Serbs are the aggressors who are 
forcing 
their way into an area which the United Nations has already 
described as a safe area. The Danish foreign minister also said 
that the Serb aggression has come at a surprising point in time 
when "there was a hope that more peaceful developments were 
underway. And then suddenly the Serbs launch this massive 
attack on one of the safe areas." 
  A spokeswoman for UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
said yesterday evening that the general secretary had not 
hesitated to use force in the defense of the Muslim enclave of 
Gorazde. Nor will he hesitate to do so again, spokeswoman 
Therese Gastaut said. 

</TEXT>

