<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Suggests `Extremist' Role in Border Event </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1204122794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1204122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said today 
that Greece regrets the incident on the Greek-Albanian border 
and stressed that when real incidents occur, Greece is willing 
to cooperate to clear up the issue on the level of the judicial 
authorities. Venizelos noted that Greece will not get carried 
away by the climate of tension cultivated by the Albanian side, 
because its goal is to safeguard peace in the southern Balkans. 
  The spokesman added that the only information Greece has in 
connection with these incidents is that provided by the Albanian 
side. Venizelos added: No one can rule out the existence of 
extremist elements but these are elements that are handled by a 
state that operates in an excellent fashion. The spokesman 
concluded by saying that Greece will accept no provocation 
against it. 

</TEXT>

