<H3> <TI>   Croatian Minister Granic Arrives in Ankara </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Croatian Minister Granic Arrives in Ankara </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1204170194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1204170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Mate Granic, Croatian foreign affairs and deputy 
prime minister, has arrived in Ankara on an official visit. 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin received the guest minister at 
Ankara's Esenboga Airport. 
  In statement he issued at the airport, Cetin said Turkey and 
Croatia play a very important role in solving the conflict in 
former Yugoslavia. Indicating that Granic personally 
contributed to the agreement signed between the Croats and the 
Bosnians, Cetin said that the agreement is a significant step 
toward peace. Cetin stated that Turkey is among the countries 
which requested to participate in the peace forces in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and added that this issue will be discussed 
during his visit. Cetin announced that an aviation agreement 
will be signed with Croatia. 
  Granic, in turn, stressed Turkey is an important country 
regarding the protection of peace and stability in the region 
and in the Balkans. Granic noted that future work regarding the 
agreement signed between the Bosnians and the Croats will be 
assessed during this visit. 

</TEXT>

