<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Bulgarian Defense Minister Valentin Aleksandrov, 
who arrived on an official visit to Ankara, has begun his 
contacts. On his arrival at the National Defense Ministry, 
Aleksandrov was received by National Defense Minister Mehmet 
Golhan with a military ceremony. In a statement at the meeting, 
Golhan said that Bulgaria's relations with Turkey have developed 
after that country's transition to democracy. Aleksandrov 
stressed that Bulgaria's relations with Turkey are developing in 
the field of defense industry. 
  Aleksandrov later called on Chief of Staff General Dogan 
Gures. At the meeting, Gures said that if the aggressors in the 
Balkans are not punished this will set an example and lead to 
graver results. Pointing out that the fighting in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina is not between soldiers but that the Serbs 
are killing civilians, women and children, Gures expressed 
satisfaction over the NATO operation against the Serbs. 
Aleksandrov said that Bulgaria favors securing peace without 
resorting to arms in the Balkans. 

