<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Demands Stop To Serb Attack on Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe Demands Stop To Serb Attack on Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204175594 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Paris this afternoon, Foreign Minister Alain 
Juppe gave an explanation to deputies about the situation in 
Bosnia. 
  [Begin Juppe recording] First, of course, we have to put an 
end to the Serb offensive against Gorazde, without delay and 
without conditions. This resolution must not waver. Of course, 
France, which is part of the air support contingent, will face 
up to all its responsibilities as far as this is concerned. 
  But equally, in order to prevent a potentially never-ending 
escalation, we have to set precise political aims for our action 
in Gorazde, starting with an immediate cease-fire, and, second, 
the deployment of the UN Protection Force [UNPROFOR] on the 
ground to act as a buffer between the communities. We are 
contemplating the possibility of a Security Council resolution 
to this end. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

