<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Brinkman Intends To Stay On in </F>
Controversial Job"] 
  [Excerpt] Elco Brinkman, CDA [Christian Democratic Appeal 
Party] leader, for the time being, will stay on as a board 
member of Arscop BV, a company that manages the accounts of a 
firm whose management is suspected of tax fraud. When the 
company was raided a pistol was also found. 
  "I am in contact with my fellow board members about this 
situation and the accusation that has been made," Brinkman said 
last weekend. In a program broadcast Friday evening [8 April] 
on the KRO [Catholic Radio Broadcasting Company] series 
"Reporter," it was maintained that Brinkman must have known 
about the alleged fraud. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

