<F P=100> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPD Criticizes Military Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Criticizes Military Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304142394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1324 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1304142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The Social Democratic Party 
[SPD] has strongly criticized the German Government's military 
aid for Turkey. It has never been clarified whether these 
weapons have been used against Kurds, SPD Bundestag group 
chairman Hans-Ulrich Klose said in the Bundestag today. If the 
German Foreign Ministry is now requesting proof of such 
allegations from human rights groups, then this is "evidence of 
a miserable failure on the part of the Foreign Ministry over 
many years." 
  Klose advocated civilian CSCE observers investigating 
conditions in Turkey. German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
(Free Democratic Party [FDP]) must launch a relevant initiative 
immediately. The CSCE has responsibility for this, not least 
because the conflict is threatening to extend beyond Turkey. 
  Klose added that Germany is greatly affected because the 
Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) does not shrink back from 
terrorism even in the Federal Republic. This is unacceptable. 
Klose stressed that those who abuse the right to hospitality 
must be "prosecuted, sentenced, and expelled." However, the 
expulsion orders can only be executed "if, in each individual 
case, proof is furnished that the deportee will not be tortured 
or killed in Turkey." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

