<H3> <TI>   UN To Evacuate German Engineers in Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN To Evacuate German Engineers in Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304140994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1210 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1304140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali has announced that the Deutsche Welle employees 
left behind in the Rwandan capital of Kigali are to be evacuated 
by UN troops. His information was that the situation in the 
vicinity of the Deutsche Welle relay station is still quiet at 
present, Butrus-Ghali said in Bonn today. It is planned to 
evacuate the Germans with the aid of helicopters. German 
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel (Free Democratic Party) expressly 
thanked the UN secretary general for the UN support in the 
evacuation of German citizens from Rwanda. 

