<H3> <TI>   Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1204112494 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1204112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong is in Germany for a 
four-day official visit. Mr. Goh, who is making his first trip 
to Germany as prime minister, is accompanied by three cabinet 
ministers and 14 high-ranking businessmen. Tomorrow, Mr. Goh 
will hold talks with Chancellor Helmut Kohl. The two leaders 
will also witness the signing of the German-Singapore Business 
Forum by private sectors from both sides. The forum is intended 
to promote business tie-ups in the Asia-Pacific region. Mr. 
Goh's trip, which will also take him to Britain next week, is 
seeking to sell Singapore's new economic strategy to European 
businessmen. 

</TEXT>

